# ==========================================
# REQUIRED ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ==========================================
# 游늶 Create a .env file in the root with these CRITICAL variables:
#
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION
# 較럭 MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database
#
# OPENAI CONFIGURATION
# 較럭 OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...your-api-key...
#
# EMAIL SERVICE (SMTP)
# 較럭 EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# 較럭 EMAIL_PORT=587
# 較럭 EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# 較럭 EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-app-password (NOT your Gmail password!)
#    Note: For Gmail, generate an App Password:
#    https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#
# OPTIONAL CONFIGURATION
# 較럭 ENABLE_SCHEDULERS=false (set to true to enable background jobs)
# 較럭 PORT=5000
#
# ==========================================
# DEPENDENCIES INSTALLED VIA NPM
# ==========================================
# Core Dependencies (in package.json):
# 較럭 express: ^5.2.1           (REST API framework)
# 較럭 mongoose: ^9.0.2          (MongoDB ORM)
# 較럭 openai: ^6.15.0           (OpenAI GPT API client)
# 較럭 nodemailer: ^7.0.12       (Email sending)
# 較럭 rss-parser: ^3.13.0       (RSS feed parsing)
# 較럭 axios: ^1.13.2            (HTTP client)
# 較럭 cheerio: ^1.1.2           (HTML/XML parsing)
# 較럭 dotenv: ^17.2.3           (Environment variables)
# 較럭 cors: ^2.8.5              (CORS middleware)
# 較럭 node-cron: ^4.2.1         (Task scheduling)
# 較럭 cron: ^4.4.0              (Cron expressions)
# 較럭 zod: ^4.2.1               (Data validation)
#
# Dev Dependencies:
# 較덕 nodemon: ^3.1.11          (Auto-restart on file changes)
#
# Install all: npm install
#
# ==========================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ==========================================
# 1. Setup MongoDB:
#    - Create cluster on MongoDB Atlas
#    - Generate connection string
#    - Add to MONGODB_URI in .env
#
# 2. Setup OpenAI:
#    - Create API key at https://platform.openai.com/
#    - Add to OPENAI_API_KEY in .env
#
# 3. Setup Email (Gmail):
#    - Enable 2-Factor Authentication
#    - Generate App Password at https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#    - Use App Password in EMAIL_PASSWORD (NOT your Gmail password!)
#
# 4. Run Server:
#    npm start        (production)
#    npm run dev      (development with auto-reload)
#
# 5. Test Health:
#    curl http://localhost:5000/health
#
# ==========================================
